objenome.problem

Class STGPBoolean

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.AbstractPrototainer
      • objenome.Container
        • objenome.solver.evolve.GPContainer<TypedOrganism>
          • objenome.problem.ProblemSTGP
            • objenome.problem.STGPBoolean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractContainer, Prototainer

    public class STGPBoolean
extends ProblemSTGP
    This template sets up EpochX to run the 6-bit multiplexer benchmark with the STGP representation. The 6-bit multiplexer problem involves evolving a program which receives an array of 6 boolean values. The first 2 values are address bits, which the program should convert into an index for which of the remaining data registers to return. {a0, a1, d0, d1, d2, d3}.
    a0a1return value falsefalsed0 truefalsed1 falsetrued2 truetrued3
    The following configuration is used:
  • Population.SIZE: 100
  • EvolutionaryStrategy.TERMINATION_CRITERIA: MaximumGenerations, TerminationFitness(0.0)
  • MaximumGenerations.MAXIMUM_GENERATIONS: 50
  • TypedOrganism.MAXIMUM_DEPTH: 6
  • Breeder.SELECTOR: TournamentSelector
  • TournamentSelector#TOURNAMENT_SIZE: 7
  • Breeder.OPERATORS: SubtreeCrossover, SubtreeMutation
  • SubtreeMutation.PROBABILITY: 0.0
  • SubtreeCrossover.PROBABILITY: 1.0
  • Initialiser.METHOD: FullInitialisation
  • RandomSequence.RANDOM_SEQUENCE: MersenneTwisterFast
  • TypedOrganism.SYNTAX: AndFunction, OrFunction, NotFunction, IfFunction, VariableNode("A0", Boolean), VariableNode("A1", Boolean), VariableNode("D2", Boolean), VariableNode("D3", Boolean), VariableNode("D4", Boolean), VariableNode("D5", Boolean)
  • TypedOrganism.RETURN_TYPE: Boolean
  • FitnessEvaluator.FUNCTION: HitsCount
  • TypedFitnessFunction.INPUT_VARIABLES: A0, A1, D2, D3, D4, D5
  • TypedFitnessFunction.INPUT_VALUE_SETS: [all possible binary input combinations]
  • HitsCount.EXPECTED_OUTPUTS: [correct output for input value sets]
